    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>HTTPS Interactive Explorer</title>\n<style>\n  body { font-family: monospace, monospace; background: white; color: black; margin: 1em; }\n  textarea, input, select, button { font-family: monospace; font-size: 1em; margin: 0.2em 0; width: 100%; max-width: 600px; }\n  label { display: block; margin-top: 1em; }\n  .section { margin-bottom: 2em; border-top: 1px solid #000; padding-top: 1em; }\n  pre { background: #eee; padding: 1em; max-height: 200px; overflow: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; }\n  .inline { display: inline-block; width: auto; margin-right: 0.5em; }\n  button { width: auto; }\n  input[type=checkbox] { width: auto; }\n  select { width: auto; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>HTTPS Interactive Explorer</h1>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"overview\">\n  <p>\n    This interactive tool lets you explore HTTPS (HTTP over TLS/SSL) in depth through user-driven workflows.\n    You can build connections, configure encryption parameters, simulate certificate validation,\n    inspect HTTP request & response layers, manipulate TLS handshake steps, and test security features.\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"server-setup\">\n<h2>1. Server Setup</h2>\n<label>\n  Server Domain (Common Name for Cert):<br />\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"server-domain\" placeholder=\"example.com\" value=\"example.com\" />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Choose Certificate Type:<br />\n  <select id=\"cert-type\">\n    <option value=\"self-signed\">Self-Signed Certificate</option>\n    <option value=\"valid-root\">Valid CA-Signed Certificate</option>\n    <option value=\"expired\">Expired Certificate</option>\n    <option value=\"revoked\">Revoked Certificate</option>\n    <option value=\"mismatch\">Domain Mismatch Certificate</option>\n  </select>\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Certificate Validity Start (YYYY-MM-DD):<br />\n  <input type=\"date\" id=\"cert-valid-from\" />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Certificate Validity End (YYYY-MM-DD):<br />\n  <input type=\"date\" id=\"cert-valid-to\" />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Revoked (simulate CRL/OCSP): <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"cert-revoked\" />\n</label>\n\n<button id=\"generate-cert\">Generate Certificate</button>\n\n<pre id=\"cert-output\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"tls-settings\">\n<h2>2. TLS Configuration</h2>\n\n<label>\n  TLS Version:<br />\n  <select id=\"tls-version\">\n    <option value=\"1.0\">TLS 1.0</option>\n    <option value=\"1.1\">TLS 1.1</option>\n    <option value=\"1.2\" selected>TLS 1.2</option>\n    <option value=\"1.3\">TLS 1.3</option>\n  </select>\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Cipher Suites (multiple select, hold Ctrl/Cmd):<br />\n  <select id=\"cipher-suites\" multiple size=\"6\">\n    <option value=\"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA\">TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA</option>\n    <option value=\"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA\">TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA</option>\n    <option value=\"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256\" selected>TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256</option>\n    <option value=\"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384\" selected>TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384</option>\n    <option value=\"TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256\">TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 (TLS 1.3)</option>\n    <option value=\"TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384\">TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 (TLS 1.3)</option>\n  </select>\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Enable Forward Secrecy: <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"forward-secrecy\" checked />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Enable OCSP Stapling: <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"ocsp-stapling\" />\n</label>\n\n<button id=\"simulate-handshake\">Simulate TLS Handshake</button>\n<pre id=\"handshake-log\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"certificate-validation\">\n<h2>3. Certificate Validation</h2>\n<p>Simulate client certificate validation given the certificate and current date.</p>\n\n<label>\n  Client Date (for validation):<br />\n  <input type=\"date\" id=\"client-date\" />\n</label>\n\n<button id=\"validate-cert\">Validate Certificate</button>\n\n<pre id=\"validation-result\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"http-requests\">\n<h2>4. HTTP Request over HTTPS</h2>\n\n<label>\n  HTTP Method: \n  <select id=\"http-method\">\n    <option>GET</option>\n    <option>POST</option>\n    <option>PUT</option>\n    <option>DELETE</option>\n    <option>HEAD</option>\n    <option>OPTIONS</option>\n  </select>\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Request Path:<br />\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"request-path\" value=\"/index.html\" />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Request Headers (one per line, format: Header-Name: value):<br />\n  <textarea id=\"request-headers\" rows=\"5\">User-Agent: HTTPS Interactive Explorer\nAccept: text/html</textarea>\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  Request Body (only for POST/PUT):<br />\n  <textarea id=\"request-body\" rows=\"5\" disabled></textarea>\n</label>\n\n<button id=\"send-request\">Send HTTPS Request</button>\n\n<pre id=\"response-output\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"https-settings-advanced\">\n<h2>5. Advanced HTTPS Settings</h2>\n\n<label class=\"inline\">\n  Enable HSTS:\n  <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"enable-hsts\" />\n</label>\n\n<label class=\"inline\">\n  HSTS max-age (seconds):\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"hsts-maxage\" value=\"31536000\" min=\"0\" />\n</label>\n\n<br />\n\n<label class=\"inline\">\n  Enable HTTP/2 Protocol:\n  <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"enable-http2\" />\n</label>\n\n<label class=\"inline\">\n  Enable ALPN Negotiation in handshake:\n  <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"enable-alpn\" />\n</label>\n\n<label>\n  ALPN Protocols (comma separated, e.g. h2,http/1.1):<br />\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"alpn-protocols\" value=\"h2,http/1.1\" />\n</label>\n\n<button id=\"restart-connection\">Restart HTTPS Connection</button>\n\n<pre id=\"advanced-log\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"state-summary\">\n<h2>Current HTTPS Connection State</h2>\n<pre id=\"state-output\"></pre>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Internal state\n  const state = {\n    server: {\n      domain: \"example.com\",\n      certType: \"self-signed\",\n      validFrom: null,\n      validTo: null,\n      revoked: false,\n      cert: null,\n    },\n    tls: {\n      version: \"1.2\",\n      cipherSuites: [\n        \"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256\",\n        \"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384\",\n      ],\n      forwardSecrecy: true,\n      ocspStapling: false,\n      handshakeLog: [],\n      sessionEstablished: false,\n      negotiatedALPN: null,\n    },\n    validation: {\n      clientDate: null,\n      result: \"\",\n    },\n    http: {\n      method: \"GET\",\n      path: \"/index.html\",\n      headers: {\n        \"User-Agent\": \"HTTPS Interactive Explorer\",\n        Accept: \"text/html\",\n      },\n      body: \"\",\n      response: null,\n    },\n    httpsSettings: {\n      hstsEnabled: false,\n      hstsMaxAge: 31536000,\n      http2: false,\n      alpnEnabled: false,\n      alpnProtocols: [\"h2\", \"http/1.1\"],\n    },\n  };\n\n  // Utility functions\n  function dateStringToDate(str) {\n    if (!str) return null;\n    const d = new Date(str + \"T00:00:00Z\");\n    return isNaN(d.getTime()) ? null : d;\n  }\n\n  function formatDate(d) {\n    if (!d) return \"(none)\";\n    return d.toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n  }\n\n  function deepClone(obj) {\n    return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj));\n  }\n\n  function parseHeaders(str) {\n    // Parse header lines like \"Name: value\"\n    const lines = str.split(\"\\n\");\n    const headers = {};\n    for (const line of lines) {\n      const i = line.indexOf(\":\");\n      if (i > 0) {\n        const name = line.slice(0, i).trim();\n        const value = line.slice(i + 1).trim();\n        if (name && value) {\n          headers[name] = value;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    return headers;\n  }\n\n  // Certificate generation simulation\n  function generateCertificate() {\n    /*\n      Certificates will be represented as objects:\n\n      {\n        subject: { CN: string },\n        issuer: { CN: string },\n        validFrom: Date,\n        validTo: Date,\n        serialNumber: string,\n        signatureAlgorithm: string,\n        publicKeyAlgorithm: string,\n        publicKey: string,\n        isSelfSigned: boolean,\n        revoked: boolean,\n        extensions: {...}\n      }\n    */\n\n    const domain = document.getElementById(\"server-domain\").value.trim() || \"example.com\";\n    const certType = document.getElementById(\"cert-type\").value;\n    const validFromStr = document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-from\").value;\n    const validToStr = document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-to\").value;\n    const revoked = document.getElementById(\"cert-revoked\").checked;\n\n    // Default dates if none set\n    let validFrom = dateStringToDate(validFromStr);\n    let validTo = dateStringToDate(validToStr);\n    if (!validFrom) validFrom = new Date(Date.now()-1000*60*60*24*365);\n    if (!validTo) validTo = new Date(Date.now()+1000*60*60*24*365);\n\n    let issuerCN, isSelfSigned;\n\n    if(certType === \"self-signed\") {\n      issuerCN = domain;\n      isSelfSigned = true;\n    } else if(certType === \"valid-root\") {\n      issuerCN = \"Trusted Root CA\";\n      isSelfSigned = false;\n    } else if(certType === \"expired\") {\n      issuerCN = \"Trusted Root CA\";\n      isSelfSigned = false;\n      // Override dates to past\n      validFrom = new Date(Date.now()-1000*60*60*24*730);\n      validTo = new Date(Date.now()-1000*60*60*24*365);\n    } else if(certType === \"revoked\") {\n      issuerCN = \"Trusted Root CA\";\n      isSelfSigned = false;\n    } else if(certType === \"mismatch\") {\n      issuerCN = \"Trusted Root CA\";\n      isSelfSigned = false;\n    } else {\n      issuerCN = \"Trusted Root CA\";\n      isSelfSigned = false;\n    }\n\n    // For mismatch, subject CN differs from domain\n    const subjectCN = certType === \"mismatch\" ? \"wrongdomain.com\" : domain;\n\n    // Build a fake serial number\n    const serialNumber = Math.floor(Math.random()*1e16).toString(16).toUpperCase();\n\n    // Fake public key algorithm\n    const publicKeyAlgorithm = \"RSA\";\n\n    // Fake signature algorithm\n    let signatureAlgorithm = \"sha256WithRSAEncryption\";\n\n    if (state.tls.version === \"1.3\") {\n      signatureAlgorithm = \"ed25519\";\n    }\n\n    const cert = {\n      subject: { CN: subjectCN },\n      issuer: { CN: issuerCN },\n      validFrom,\n      validTo,\n      serialNumber,\n      signatureAlgorithm,\n      publicKeyAlgorithm,\n      publicKey: publicKeyAlgorithm + \" Public Key Data\",\n      isSelfSigned,\n      revoked: certType === \"revoked\" || revoked,\n      extensions: {\n        keyUsage: [\"Digital Signature\", \"Key Encipherment\"],\n        extendedKeyUsage: [\"TLS Web Server Authentication\"],\n        basicConstraints: { CA: false },\n        subjectAltName: [subjectCN],\n      },\n    };\n\n    state.server.domain = domain;\n    state.server.certType = certType;\n    state.server.validFrom = validFrom;\n    state.server.validTo = validTo;\n    state.server.revoked = cert.revoked;\n    state.server.cert = cert;\n\n    // Show cert dump\n    let out = \"=== Simulated Certificate ===\\n\";\n    out += `Subject CN: ${cert.subject.CN}\\nIssuer CN: ${cert.issuer.CN}\\n`;\n    out += `Validity: ${formatDate(cert.validFrom)} to ${formatDate(cert.validTo)}\\n`;\n    out += `Serial Number: ${cert.serialNumber}\\n`;\n    out += `Signature Algorithm: ${cert.signatureAlgorithm}\\n`;\n    out += `Public Key Algorithm: ${cert.publicKeyAlgorithm}\\n`;\n    out += `Is Self-Signed: ${cert.isSelfSigned}\\n`;\n    out += `Revoked: ${cert.revoked}\\n`;\n    out += `Extensions:\\n  Key Usage: ${cert.extensions.keyUsage.join(\", \")}\\n  Extended Key Usage: ${cert.extensions.extendedKeyUsage.join(\", \")}\\n  Basic Constraints - CA: ${cert.extensions.basicConstraints.CA}\\n  Subject Alternative Name(s): ${cert.extensions.subjectAltName.join(\", \")}\\n`;\n    return out;\n  }\n\n\n  // TLS handshake simulation\n  function simulateTLSHandshake() {\n    const log = [];\n    log.push(\"Starting TLS Handshake Simulation...\");\n\n    // Setup parameters from inputs\n    const tlsVersion = document.getElementById(\"tls-version\").value;\n    const cipherSelect = document.getElementById(\"cipher-suites\");\n    const selectedCiphers = Array.from(cipherSelect.selectedOptions).map(o => o.value);\n    if(selectedCiphers.length === 0) {\n      log.push(\"Warning: No cipher suites selected. Handshake aborted.\");\n      state.tls.handshakeLog = log;\n      state.tls.sessionEstablished = false;\n      state.tls.negotiatedALPN = null;\n      return log;\n    }\n    const forwardSecrecy = document.getElementById(\"forward-secrecy\").checked;\n    const ocspStapling = document.getElementById(\"ocsp-stapling\").checked;\n    const alpnEnabled = document.getElementById(\"enable-alpn\").checked;\n    const alpnProtocolsStr = document.getElementById(\"alpn-protocols\").value;\n    const alpnProtocols = alpnProtocolsStr.split(\",\").map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n\n    state.tls.version = tlsVersion;\n    state.tls.cipherSuites = selectedCiphers;\n    state.tls.forwardSecrecy = forwardSecrecy;\n    state.tls.ocspStapling = ocspStapling;\n\n    let cert = state.server.cert;\n    if(!cert) {\n      log.push(\"Error: No certificate loaded. Aborting handshake.\");\n      state.tls.sessionEstablished = false;\n      state.tls.negotiatedALPN = null;\n      state.tls.handshakeLog = log;\n      return log;\n    }\n\n    // Client Hello\n    log.push(`Client Hello -> TLS Version: ${tlsVersion}, Cipher Suites: ${selectedCiphers.join(\", \")}`);\n\n    // Server Hello\n    // Server must pick first compatible cipher from list by priority:\n    // Let's simulate server only supports subset:\n\n    const supportedCiphers = {\n      \"1.0\": [\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA\",\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA\"\n      ],\n      \"1.1\": [\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA\",\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA\"\n      ],\n      \"1.2\": [\n        \"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256\",\n        \"TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384\",\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA\",\n        \"TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA\"\n      ],\n      \"1.3\": [\n        \"TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256\",\n        \"TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384\"\n      ]\n    };\n\n    let serverSupported = supportedCiphers[tlsVersion];\n    let negotiatedCipher = null;\n    for(const c of selectedCiphers) {\n      if(serverSupported.includes(c)) {\n        if(forwardSecrecy) {\n          // Disallow ciphers without forward secrecy for simulation\n          // Let's consider only ECDHE or TLS1.3 ciphers as forward secrecy\n          if(tlsVersion === \"1.3\" || c.includes(\"ECDHE\")) {\n            negotiatedCipher = c;\n            break;\n          }\n        } else {\n          negotiatedCipher = c;\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    if(!negotiatedCipher) {\n      log.push(\"Server Hello -> No compatible cipher suite found with current settings.\");\n      state.tls.sessionEstablished = false;\n      state.tls.negotiatedALPN = null;\n      state.tls.handshakeLog = log;\n      return log;\n    }\n\n    log.push(`Server Hello -> Selected Cipher Suite: ${negotiatedCipher}`);\n\n    // ALPN negotiation if enabled & supported by TLS version >= 1.2\n    let negotiatedALPN = null;\n    if(alpnEnabled && (tlsVersion === \"1.2\" || tlsVersion === \"1.3\") && alpnProtocols.length > 0) {\n      const serverSupportedAlpns = [\"h2\",\"http/1.1\"];\n      // find first client ALPN that server supports\n      for(const proto of alpnProtocols) {\n        if(serverSupportedAlpns.includes(proto)) {\n          negotiatedALPN = proto;\n          log.push(`ALPN Negotiation -> Negotiated Protocol: ${proto}`);\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n      if(!negotiatedALPN) {\n        log.push(\"ALPN Negotiation -> No matching protocol found.\");\n      }\n    } else {\n      log.push(\"ALPN Negotiation -> Not performed or unsupported.\");\n    }\n\n    // Server Certificate Send\n    log.push(\"Server sends Certificate.\");\n    log.push(`Certificate Subject CN: ${cert.subject.CN}`);\n    log.push(`Certificate Issuer CN: ${cert.issuer.CN}`);\n\n    // Server sends Certificate Status if OCSP stapling enabled and TLS1.2 or 1.3\n    if(ocspStapling && (tlsVersion === \"1.2\" || tlsVersion === \"1.3\")) {\n      if(cert.revoked) {\n        log.push(\"OCSP Stapling -> Server sends revoked status for certificate.\");\n      } else {\n        log.push(\"OCSP Stapling -> Server sends certificate status: good.\");\n      }\n    } else {\n      log.push(\"OCSP Stapling -> Not used.\");\n    }\n\n    // Simulated handshake key exchange steps depending on cipher suite\n    if(negotiatedCipher.includes(\"ECDHE\") || tlsVersion === \"1.3\") {\n      log.push(\"Performing ECDHE key exchange for Forward Secrecy.\");\n    } else {\n      log.push(\"Performing RSA key exchange (no Forward Secrecy).\");\n    }\n\n    // Client Certificate Validation will be simulated separately\n\n    // Finished messages\n    log.push(\"Client and Server exchange Finished messages.\");\n\n    log.push(\"Handshake complete - secure TLS session established.\");\n\n    state.tls.sessionEstablished = true;\n    state.tls.negotiatedALPN = negotiatedALPN;\n    state.tls.handshakeLog = log;\n\n    return log;\n  }\n\n  // Certificate validation simulation\n  function validateCertificate() {\n    const clientDateStr = document.getElementById(\"client-date\").value;\n    const clientDate = dateStringToDate(clientDateStr) || new Date();\n    state.validation.clientDate = clientDate;\n\n    let cert = state.server.cert;\n    let res = [];\n\n    if(!cert) {\n      res.push(\"No certificate to validate.\");\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    }\n\n    res.push(\"Starting Certificate Validation...\");\n    res.push(`Client Validation Date: ${formatDate(clientDate)}`);\n\n    // 1. Check validity period\n    if(clientDate < cert.validFrom) {\n      res.push(`Certificate not yet valid (valid from ${formatDate(cert.validFrom)}). Validation failed.`);\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    }\n    if(clientDate > cert.validTo) {\n      res.push(`Certificate expired (valid to ${formatDate(cert.validTo)}). Validation failed.`);\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    }\n    res.push(\"Certificate is within validity period.\");\n\n    // 2. Check domain name matches\n    if(state.server.domain !== cert.subject.CN) {\n      res.push(`Domain mismatch: expected '${state.server.domain}', certificate for '${cert.subject.CN}'. Validation failed.`);\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    }\n    res.push(\"Domain name matches certificate subject CN.\");\n\n    // 3. Check revocation\n    if(cert.revoked) {\n      res.push(\"Certificate is revoked (CRL/OCSP). Validation failed.\");\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    }\n    res.push(\"Certificate is not revoked.\");\n\n    // 4. Check certificate chain & signature\n    if(cert.isSelfSigned) {\n      res.push(\"Certificate is self-signed: untrusted unless explicitly trusted.\");\n      res.push(\"Self-signed certificate is considered untrusted by default. Validation failed.\");\n      state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n      return state.validation.result;\n    } else {\n      res.push(\"Certificate is signed by a Trusted CA.\");\n    }\n\n    // 5. Additional checks have been skipped for simplicity\n\n    res.push(\"All standard checks passed. Certificate is valid.\");\n    state.validation.result = res.join(\"\\n\");\n    return state.validation.result;\n  }\n\n  // HTTP Request/Response simulation over HTTPS\n  function sendHTTPRequest() {\n    if(!state.tls.sessionEstablished) {\n      state.http.response = \"No secure TLS session established. Cannot send HTTP request.\\nPlease simulate TLS Handshake first.\";\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const method = document.getElementById(\"http-method\").value;\n    const path = document.getElementById(\"request-path\").value.trim() || \"/\";\n    const headerText = document.getElementById(\"request-headers\").value;\n    const headers = parseHeaders(headerText);\n\n    let body = \"\";\n    if(method === \"POST\" || method === \"PUT\") {\n      body = document.getElementById(\"request-body\").value;\n      if(body.length === 0) {\n        // Warn about empty body\n      }\n    }\n\n    state.http.method = method;\n    state.http.path = path;\n    state.http.headers = headers;\n    state.http.body = body;\n\n    // Build request header lines\n    const reqLines = [];\n    reqLines.push(`${method} ${path} HTTP/1.1`);\n    // Add Host header mandatory for HTTPS/HTTP1.1\n    if(!headers[\"Host\"]) {\n      headers[\"Host\"] = state.server.domain;\n    }\n    for(const h in headers) {\n      reqLines.push(`${h}: ${headers[h]}`);\n    }\n    reqLines.push(\"\"); // blank line separates headers from body\n\n    // Final request string to be \"sent\" over TLS\n    const reqText = reqLines.join(\"\\n\") + body;\n\n    // Simulate server HTTP response\n    // For demonstration, we simulate a minimal HTTP server with few behaviors.\n\n    let resLines = [];\n    let statusCode = 200;\n    let statusMessage = \"OK\";\n    let resHeaders = {\n      \"Date\": new Date().toUTCString(),\n      \"Server\": \"HTTPS Interactive Explorer Server\",\n      \"Content-Type\": \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\",\n      \"Content-Length\": null,\n      \"Strict-Transport-Security\": null,\n    };\n\n    // HSTS header if enabled and GET or HEAD method\n    if(state.httpsSettings.hstsEnabled && (method === \"GET\" || method === \"HEAD\")) {\n      resHeaders[\"Strict-Transport-Security\"] = `max-age=${state.httpsSettings.hstsMaxAge}`;\n    }\n\n    // Switch on path for demo responses\n    if(path === \"/\" || path === \"/index.html\") {\n      resLines.push(\"Welcome to the HTTPS Interactive Explorer!\");\n      resLines.push(\"\");\n      resLines.push(`You requested ${path} with method ${method}.`);\n      resLines.push(\"This is a simulated HTTP response over HTTPS.\");\n      if(state.tls.negotiatedALPN) {\n        resLines.push(`Negotiated ALPN protocol: ${state.tls.negotiatedALPN}`);\n      }\n      resLines.push(`TLS version in use: ${state.tls.version}`);\n      resLines.push(`Cipher suite in use: ${state.tls.cipherSuites[0]}`);\n    } else if(path === \"/echo\" && (method === \"POST\" || method === \"PUT\")) {\n      resLines.push(\"Echoing POST/PUT body:\");\n      resLines.push(body || \"(empty body)\");\n    } else if(path === \"/certinfo\") {\n      const c = state.server.cert;\n      if(c) {\n        resLines.push(\"Server Certificate Info:\");\n        resLines.push(`Subject CN: ${c.subject.CN}`);\n        resLines.push(`Issuer CN: ${c.issuer.CN}`);\n        resLines.push(`Valid From: ${formatDate(c.validFrom)}`);\n        resLines.push(`Valid To: ${formatDate(c.validTo)}`);\n        resLines.push(`Revoked: ${c.revoked}`);\n      } else {\n        resLines.push(\"No certificate information available.\");\n      }\n    } else if(path === \"/notfound\") {\n      statusCode = 404;\n      statusMessage = \"Not Found\";\n      resLines.push(\"404 Not Found: The requested resource was not found on this server.\");\n    } else {\n      statusCode = 200;\n      statusMessage = \"OK\";\n      resLines.push(`Requested resource: ${path} (no specific content)`);\n    }\n\n    const resBody = resLines.join(\"\\n\");\n    resHeaders[\"Content-Length\"] = resBody.length.toString();\n\n    // Compose HTTP response string\n    let resTextLines = [];\n    let versionText = \"HTTP/1.1\";\n    if(state.httpsSettings.http2) {\n      // HTTP/2 does not use this textual header format,\n      // but we simulate it here as textual response\n      versionText = \"HTTP/2 (simulated text response)\";\n    }\n    resTextLines.push(`${versionText} ${statusCode} ${statusMessage}`);\n\n    for(const h in resHeaders) {\n      if(resHeaders[h] !== null) {\n        resTextLines.push(`${h}: ${resHeaders[h]}`);\n      }\n    }\n    resTextLines.push(\"\"); // blank line\n    if(method !== \"HEAD\") {\n      resTextLines.push(resBody);\n    }\n\n    const resText = resTextLines.join(\"\\n\");\n\n    state.http.response = `--- HTTP Request ---\\n${reqText}\\n\\n--- HTTP Response ---\\n${resText}`;\n  }\n\n  // Advanced settings handler\n  function applyAdvancedSettings() {\n    const hstsEnabled = document.getElementById(\"enable-hsts\").checked;\n    const hstsMaxAge = parseInt(document.getElementById(\"hsts-maxage\").value) || 0;\n    const http2 = document.getElementById(\"enable-http2\").checked;\n    const alpnEnabled = document.getElementById(\"enable-alpn\").checked;\n    const alpnProtocols = document.getElementById(\"alpn-protocols\").value.split(\",\").map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n\n    state.httpsSettings.hstsEnabled = hstsEnabled;\n    state.httpsSettings.hstsMaxAge = hstsMaxAge;\n    state.httpsSettings.http2 = http2;\n    state.httpsSettings.alpnEnabled = alpnEnabled;\n    state.httpsSettings.alpnProtocols = alpnProtocols;\n\n    // Log for user\n    let advLog = [];\n    advLog.push(\"Applied Advanced HTTPS Settings:\");\n    advLog.push(`HSTS Enabled: ${hstsEnabled} (max-age=${hstsMaxAge})`);\n    advLog.push(`HTTP/2 Enabled: ${http2}`);\n    advLog.push(`ALPN Enabled: ${alpnEnabled}`);\n    advLog.push(`ALPN Protocols: ${alpnProtocols.join(\", \")}`);\n\n    // We simulate teardown and restart HTTPS session\n    state.tls.sessionEstablished = false;\n    state.tls.handshakeLog = [];\n    state.tls.negotiatedALPN = null;\n\n    return advLog.join(\"\\n\");\n  }\n\n  // Update UI elements and handlers\n  function updateRequestBodyState() {\n    const method = document.getElementById(\"http-method\").value;\n    const bodyField = document.getElementById(\"request-body\");\n    if(method === \"POST\" || method === \"PUT\") {\n      bodyField.disabled = false;\n    } else {\n      bodyField.disabled = true;\n      bodyField.value = \"\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Show current connection state\n  function showState() {\n    const s = state;\n    const lines = [];\n    lines.push(\"=== HTTPS Connection State ===\");\n    lines.push(`Server Domain: ${s.server.domain}`);\n    lines.push(`Certificate Type: ${s.server.certType}`);\n    lines.push(`Certificate Validity: ${formatDate(s.server.validFrom)} to ${formatDate(s.server.validTo)}`);\n    lines.push(`Certificate Revoked: ${s.server.revoked}`);\n    lines.push(`TLS Version: ${s.tls.version}`);\n    lines.push(`Cipher Suites Offered: ${s.tls.cipherSuites.join(\", \")}`);\n    lines.push(`Forward Secrecy Enabled: ${s.tls.forwardSecrecy}`);\n    lines.push(`OCSP Stapling Enabled: ${s.tls.ocspStapling}`);\n    lines.push(`TLS Session Established: ${s.tls.sessionEstablished}`);\n    lines.push(`Negotiated ALPN Protocol: ${s.tls.negotiatedALPN || \"(none)\"}`);\n    lines.push(`HSTS Enabled: ${s.httpsSettings.hstsEnabled}`);\n    lines.push(`HSTS Max-Age: ${s.httpsSettings.hstsMaxAge}`);\n    lines.push(`HTTP/2 Enabled: ${s.httpsSettings.http2}`);\n    lines.push(`ALPN Enabled: ${s.httpsSettings.alpnEnabled}`);\n    lines.push(`ALPN Protocols: ${s.httpsSettings.alpnProtocols.join(\", \")}`);\n    lines.push(`Last Certificate Validation Result:\\n${s.validation.result || \"(not performed yet)\"}`);\n\n    lines.push(`Last TLS Handshake Log:\\n${s.tls.handshakeLog.length > 0 ? s.tls.handshakeLog.join(\"\\n\") : \"(no handshake performed)\"}`);\n\n    lines.push(`Last HTTP Response:\\n${s.http.response || \"(no HTTP request sent yet)\"}`);\n\n    return lines.join(\"\\n\\n\");\n  }\n\n\n  // Element refs\n  const certOutput = document.getElementById(\"cert-output\");\n  const handshakeLog = document.getElementById(\"handshake-log\");\n  const validationResult = document.getElementById(\"validation-result\");\n  const responseOutput = document.getElementById(\"response-output\");\n  const advancedLog = document.getElementById(\"advanced-log\");\n  const stateOutput = document.getElementById(\"state-output\");\n\n  // Events\n  document.getElementById(\"generate-cert\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const out = generateCertificate();\n    certOutput.textContent = out;\n    // Reset validation and handshake on new cert\n    validationResult.textContent = \"\";\n    handshakeLog.textContent = \"\";\n    responseOutput.textContent = \"\";\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById(\"simulate-handshake\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const log = simulateTLSHandshake();\n    handshakeLog.textContent = log.join(\"\\n\");\n    responseOutput.textContent = \"\";\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById(\"validate-cert\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const res = validateCertificate();\n    validationResult.textContent = res;\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById(\"send-request\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    sendHTTPRequest();\n    responseOutput.textContent = state.http.response;\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById(\"http-method\").addEventListener(\"change\", () => {\n    updateRequestBodyState();\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById(\"restart-connection\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const log = applyAdvancedSettings();\n    advancedLog.textContent = log;\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n    handshakeLog.textContent = \"\";\n    responseOutput.textContent = \"\";\n    validationResult.textContent = \"\";\n  });\n\n\n  // Initialize some fields\n  function init() {\n    // Set default cert validity dates to today and 1 year later\n    let todayISO = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n    let nextYearDate = new Date();\n    nextYearDate.setFullYear(nextYearDate.getFullYear()+1);\n    let nextYearISO = nextYearDate.toISOString().slice(0,10);\n\n    if(!document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-from\").value) {\n      document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-from\").value = todayISO;\n    }\n    if(!document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-to\").value) {\n      document.getElementById(\"cert-valid-to\").value = nextYearISO;\n    }\n    document.getElementById(\"client-date\").value = todayISO;\n\n    updateRequestBodyState();\n    stateOutput.textContent = showState();\n  }\n\n  init();\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
